# Embedded Light Monitoring System

## Overview

In this project I built a small system to measure and display light intensity in real time.

The setup uses a RP2040 microcontroller together with an OPT4048 sensor.
The data is sent to a Python desktop application where it is displayed using a simple GUI.

The goal was mainly to learn how embedded systems and desktop applications can work together.

---

## Technologies

* Adafruit Feather RP2040
* OPT4048 light sensor
* C / Arduino
* Python (PyQt6)

---

## Features

* Reads light sensor data
* Sends data from the microcontroller to the PC
* Displays values in real time in a GUI
* Simple structure, easy to extend

---

## How it works

The microcontroller reads the sensor values and sends them over serial.
The Python application receives the data and updates the UI continuously.

---

## Setup

### Embedded

* Upload the code to the RP2040
* Connect the sensor

### Desktop App

```bash
pip install pyqt6
python main.py
```

---

## Notes

This is a learning project where I focused on combining embedded programming with a simple desktop interface.

---

## Possible improvements

* Add graphs instead of plain values
